main event: On June 21, 1967, a circular, silver, bright unidentified object was observed in the sky near Denver, Iowa.
interesting points: The object emitted no sound during the observation., The sighting lasted for approximately 2 minutes., The object was described as having no discernible features., It disappeared by moving behind a house., Observers included two farmers with unknown reliability.
witness description: Two farmers, ages 37 and 39, reliability unknown
